(40, 16, 8, 40, 8, 26, 26, 'O ye of little faith', 'Connection of Little Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''O ye of little faith,'' addressing the disciples'' doubts in different contexts. In Matthew 16:8, Jesus questions their reasoning about bread, while in Matthew 8:26, he addresses their fear during a storm.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
