(40, 16, 8, 43, 2, 24, 25, 'O ye of little faith', 'Understanding Faith and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' awareness of human understanding and faith. In Matthew, Jesus addresses the disciples'' lack of faith, while in John, it is noted that Jesus knows what is in man, suggesting a deeper insight into human belief and reasoning.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 8, 58, 4, 13, 13, 'O ye of little faith', 'Faith and Divine Awareness', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith and awareness of God''s presence. In Matthew, Jesus addresses the disciples'' lack of faith, while Hebrews emphasizes that all things are open to God''s sight, suggesting a call to trust in His omniscience.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 8, 43, 16, 30, 30, 'O ye of little faith', 'Faith and Understanding in Discipleship', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith and understanding among Jesus'' followers. In Matthew, Jesus addresses their lack of faith, while in John, the disciples express their belief in His divine knowledge, indicating growth in their understanding.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 8, 66, 2, 23, 23, 'O ye of little faith', 'Faith and Works Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in faith and actions. Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s beliefs and behaviors, with Matthew addressing faith and Revelation focusing on works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
