(40, 16, 9, 43, 6, 9, 13, 'five loaves of the five thousand', 'Miraculous Feeding Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous feeding of the five thousand, highlighting the use of five loaves. The mention of gathering baskets in Matthew directly recalls the twelve baskets filled in John, reinforcing the significance of the event.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 9, 40, 15, 16, 17, 'understand', 'Understanding and Comprehension', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of understanding. In Matthew 16:9, Jesus questions the disciples'' understanding of the miracle of the loaves, while in Matthew 15:16-17, He challenges their comprehension of dietary laws and their implications.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 9, 41, 6, 38, 44, 'the five loaves of the five thousand', 'Feeding of the Five Thousand', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous feeding of the five thousand with five loaves. Matthew references the event by asking about the baskets taken up, which directly relates to the account in Mark detailing the same miracle.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
