(40, 16, 11, 41, 8, 21, 21, 'How is it that ye do not understand', 'Understanding and Misunderstanding', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' lack of understanding. The phrase ''How is it that ye do not understand?'' appears in both, highlighting their confusion about Jesus'' teachings.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 16, 11, 42, 12, 56, 56, 'how is it that ye do not understand', 'Understanding Spiritual Discernment', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus urges awareness of the ''leaven'' of the Pharisees, while in Luke, He challenges the hypocrisy of failing to discern the signs of the times.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
